# Business telemetry contract

This file IS the telemetry contract. PMs propose changes by PR ("we need adoption by tenant" = one constant + one line here). Engineering reviews feasibility; CI enforces what lands.

- Ubiquitous context (`northgate.customer.id`, `northgate.tenant.id`) is set into Baggage ONCE at the request edge via `TracingSupport.withBusinessContext(...)`. NEVER set these manually on individual spans — the BaggageEnrichingSpanProcessor copies them from Baggage onto every span. Manual setting causes drift.
- Baggage is NOT automatically attached to spans. Values appear on spans only via the processor allowlist (`NorthgateAttributes.BAGGAGE_ALLOWLIST`). Do not assume a baggage entry is queryable unless the processor copies it.
- NEVER put secrets or non-allowlisted PII in Baggage. It propagates as the W3C `baggage` HTTP header to every downstream call, including third-party APIs outside our trust boundary. The egress allowlist lives in propagator configuration, not application code.
- Span-local business attributes that only the local code path knows (`northgate.order.id`, `northgate.shipment.id`) are set explicitly from `NorthgateAttributes` where this contract requires them: every span in an order- or shipment-domain package must carry the corresponding ID.
- Request-path classification: packages matching `..api..` / `..http..` or methods annotated `@RequestPath`. Spans marked `@InternalSpan` are exempt from business-attribute requirements.
